<title>How to: Display code in HTML</title>

    <h1>How to: Display code in HTML</h1>
        <p>
            Simple question, I've been wanting to try and display code inside an HTML page, <em>ie</em> this blog for a while. This in order to log my progress, and for future reference. If the code is found to be useful enough, and I have enough snippets, I will consider opening a new section on this site: "programming". This website is all custom built, HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript. Since this is the case, then there are no handy plugins to do such things for like with wordpress.
        </p>
        <p>
            So I started simply by searching for some syntax highlighting libraries. I was sure some existed, and did not want to go around making my own stylesheets and targeting HTML etc; although I must admit this was my first thought.
        </p>
        <p>
            I first came across <a href="https://highlightjs.org" target="_blank">highlight.js</a>. It seemed like a good project, but when I first tried I had some issues with the configuration so I decided to go with <a href="http://alexgorbatchev.com/SyntaxHighlighter/">SyntaxHighlighter</a> instead.
        </p>
